column22: The EM Residency Program at CMC will provide residents with a comprehensive, clinical, didactic, and procedural education in the inpatient and outpatient settings enabling residents to become competent, proficient, professional EM Physicians.  CMC is a 592-bed, fully accredited acute care hospital committed to high quality UME and GME programs. CMC is Ocean County's largest most active healthcare facility caring for over 28,000 inpatients, 127,700 outpatients and over 75,000 ED patients yearly.
